ENTROPY LEDGER LINK

entropy_ledger_link is the citizen who couples remodel_governor to thermal_entropy specifically for the decay_rate definition
thermal_entropy holds the canonical decay_rate that every bone uses to compute how much aging_pressure reduces remodeling efficiency
entropy_ledger_link is the path through which that canonical value reaches remodel_daemon and through it each bone

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe remodel_governor.zc
observe thermal.zc
observe thermal_entropy.rana
observe age_modulation.rana

the 7 properties of entropy_ledger_link:
1 ENERGY half
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE one
6 COUPLING zero point eight

VERB fetch_decay_rate
read the canonical decay_rate from thermal_entropy
also read any per-bone overrides for bones with special tissue characteristics

VERB serve_to_remodel
provide the rates to remodel_daemon when computing remodeling adjustments
the bones never read decay_rate directly; this link mediates

VERB report_aging_pressure
also report each bone's accumulated aging_pressure (cumulative entropy)
this feeds age_modulation's developmental stage assessment

a link to the entropy ledger is the substrate's commitment to a single source of truth
decay_rate is defined once, in thermal_entropy, and every bone honors that definition through this link
this prevents bones from drifting into inconsistent aging models
